Possible values are the ISO 4217 currency codes, such as "USD" for the US dollar, "EUR" for the euro, or "CNY" for the Chinese RMB. There is no default value; if the style is "currency", the currency property must be provided.

inputnumber/currencyDisplay.description: How to display the currency in currency formatting. Possible values are "symbol" to use a localized currency symbol such as , "code" to use the ISO currency code, "name" to use a localized currency name such as "dollar"; the default is "symbol".

Possible values are from 0 to 20; the default for plain number and percent formatting is 0; the default for currency formatting is the number of minor unit digits provided by the ISO 4217 currency code list (2 if the list doesn't provide that information).

inputnumber/maxFractionDigits.description: The maximum number of fraction digits to use. Possible values are from 0 to 20; the default for plain number formatting is the larger of minimumFractionDigits and 3; the default for currency formatting is the larger of minimumFractionDigits and the number of minor unit digits provided by the ISO 4217 currency code list (2 if the list doesn't provide that information).

knob/readonly.description: When present, it specifies that the component value cannot be edited.

knob/showValue.description: Whether the show the value inside the knob.

listbox/options.description: An array of selectitems to display as the available options.

listbox/optionLabel.description: Property name or getter function to use as the label of an option.

listbox/optionValue.description: Property name or getter function to use as the value of an option, defaults to the option itself when not defined.

listbox/optionDisabled.description: Property name or getter function to use as the disabled flag of an option, defaults to false when not defined.

listbox/optionGroupLabel.description: Property name or getter function to use as the label of an option group.

listbox/optionGroupChildren.description: Property name or getter function that refers to the children options of option group.

listbox/listStyle.description: Inline style of inner list element.

listbox/dataKey.description: A property to uniquely identify an option.

listbox/multiple.description: When specified, allows selecting multiple values.

listbox/metaKeySelection.description: Defines how multiple items can be selected, when true metaKey needs to be pressed to select or unselect an item and when set to false selection of each item can be toggled individually. On touch enabled devices, metaKeySelection is turned off automatically.

listbox/filter.description: When specified, displays a filter input at header.

listbox/filterPlaceholder.description: Placeholder text to show when filter input is empty.

listbox/filterLocale.description: Locale to use in filtering. The default locale is the host environment's current locale.

listbox/filterMatchMode.description: Defines the filtering algorithm to use when searching the options. Valid values are "contains" (default), "startsWith" and "endsWith"

listbox/filterFields.description: Fields used when filtering the options, defaults to optionLabel.

listbox/emptyFilterMessage.description: Text to display when filtering does not return any results. Defaults to value from PrimeVue locale configuration.

listbox/emptyMessage.description: Text to display when there are no options available. Defaults to value from PrimeVue locale configuration.

megamenu/orientation.description: Defines the orientation, valid values are horizontal and vertical.

menu/exact.description: Whether to apply 'router-link-active-exact' class if route exactly matches the item path.

According to the scrolls made up and down, extra items are added in a certain algorithm in the form of multiples of this number. Default value is half the number of items shown in the view.
